Acting metro police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Kobeli Mokheseng initially said "three or four" spaza shops had been pillaged in Lesotho Street but later adjusted this to one shop being hit."There was action between 11:00 and 15:00 today but the situation has been restored " he said. "We don t know what caused it."He said one person was injured and that no arrests have yet been made.Katlehong North police spokesperson Captain Nega Ndobe said a business was robbed last night and believed the two incidents to be linked.